Miconazole was first synthesized in 1969 and first granted FDA approval on January 8, 1974, for sale by INSIGHT Pharmaceuticals as a topical cream.[A214523, L14021] It is currently available as a variety of prescription and over the counter products. Despite having been in clinical use for an extended period, resistance to miconazole among susceptible organisms is relatively low.[A203636]', '["A07AC01", "J02AB01", "D01AC52", "G01AF20", "A01AB09", "D01AC02", "S02AA13", "G01AF04"]', '[]');
